  "body": "The docs say that we can override `clock()` and use timestamp-based governance as of 4.9: https://docs.openzeppelin.com/contracts/4.x/governance#token_2\r\n\r\nBut `block.number` is still all that is supported in Checkpoint.sol in v4.9.0: https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/blob/v4.9.0/contracts/utils/Checkpoints.sol\r\n\r\nIt is not until after 4.9 that checkpoint has the right support for timestamps:\r\n<img width=\"1216\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/assets/2158394/2cc20d81-172c-4357-8725-9dadc6188349\">\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n",
